President Biden, President Yoon, and Prime Minister Kishida held a trilateral summit to discuss their shared objective of achieving complete denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and a free and open Indo-Pacific. They expressed concern over the DPRK's continued ballistic missile tests and potential for a nuclear test. The leaders highlighted the global resolve to hold Russia accountable for its actions in Ukraine and reaffirmed their commitment to the rules-based international order. They discussed the need to upgrade the deterrence capabilities of the Japan-U.S. and U.S.-ROK alliances and agreed on trilateral missile warning and ballistic missile search and tracking exercises. They also discussed the possibility of joint exercises in response to a nuclear test. Japan expressed gratitude for support on the abduction issue and requested continued understanding and cooperation. The press conference concluded at 2:42 P.M. CEST.